I wonder if sprite 0 hit is really a "sprite $2003 hit" instead, i.e. the address in $2003 determines the sprite that should record at hit in $2002 bit 6.<br /><br />I can see why a game might load sprites at $80 every other frame, as a quick way to compensate for the eight-sprite limit imposed by the PPU.<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Tue Dec 13, 2005 10:28 am</p><hr />
