Does the sprite address (0x2003) change during rendering like the bg address (0x2006) ?<br /><br />I'm currently simply reading sprites from address 0 and up, that doesn't seem to cause problems, except for Akira (J). It locks up because it uses the sprite zero bit for its splitscreen effect. If I hack in a sprite_address=0 once per frame (or even nastier, in 0x2002: if (scanline==akirasplitline) status=status|0x40;), it works.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=115">hap</a> — Thu Aug 04, 2005 10:58 am</p><hr />
